HEADWORD: Thorough-brace
<hw>Thor"ough-brace`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A leather
strap supporting the body of a carriage, and attached to springs, or
serving as a spring. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Chaise</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thoroughbred</ent>⟦br⟧
